In [44]:
for w in [w1, w2, w3]:
    y, x = step(w)
    plt.plot(x,y,"b")
    plt.title('Step Responsse ') 
    plt.ylabel('Amplitude')
    plt.xlabel('Time(sec)')
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()
    y,x=impulse(w)
    plt.plot(x,y,"r")
    plt.title('impulse Responsse ') 
    plt.ylabel('Amplitude')
    plt.xlabel('Time(sec)')
    plt.show()
    mag, phase, omega = bode(w, dB=True)
    plt.plot()
    plt.show()
    plt.title('Nyquist Diagram ') 
    plt.ylabel('Imaginary Axis')
    plt.xlabel('Real Axis')
    nyquist(w)
    plt.plot()
    plt.show()

Дано¶

$$ W(p) = \frac{k}{Tp+1}\; $$$$ W(p) = \frac{k}{{T_{2}^2}{p^2}+{T_{1}}{p}+1}\; $$$$ W(p) = \frac{k}{{T_{u}}{p}}\; $$

In [6]:
from control import matlab as lab
a = 1
W1 = lab.tf([k*a],[T, one])
W2 = lab.tf([k*a], [T_2, T_1, one])
W3 = lab.tf([k*a], [T_u, zero])

In [20]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

fig, ax = plt.subplots(3, 1)
fig.set_size_inches(10, 25)
for i,w in enumerate([W1, W2, W3]):
    y, x = lab.step(w)
    ax[i].set_title(f'W{i+1}') 
    ax[i].set_ylabel('Amplitude')
    ax[i].set_xlabel('Time(sec)')
    ax[i].plot(x,y,label=f'{w}')
    ax[i].grid(True)
    ax[i].legend()
